  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1170 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Preheat #oven{} to 350 degrees. Slice @fresh pork chorizo{1}(sliced into rounds). Add to a large pan over medium-high heat. Cook, tossing occasionally, until oil has rendered and rounds are crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from pan with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside, keeping as much oil in pan as possible.

Wash and dry all produce. While chorizo cooks, halve, peel, and slice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and sliced into thin slices). Slice @polenta{8%oz} into ⅓-inch-thick rounds.

Add polenta in a single layer and cook until browned and crispy, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. (TIP: Add a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} if pan seems dry.) Transfer to a #baking sheet{}. Place in oven to keep warm.

Heat another drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tsp}. Cook, tossing, until onion is softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in @diced tomatoes{1%14oz can} and bring to a boil. Lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Season to taste with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and additional Tuscan Heat Spice (to taste—it's spicy).

Add @spinach{5%oz} to pan and stir to combine. Continue simmering until spinach is wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Set aside a few rounds of chorizo for garnish, then stir remaining rounds into pan. Season with salt and pepper. Simmer until liquid is mostly evaporated, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Heat a drizzle of oil in another large pan over medium-high heat. Crack @eggs{2} into pan and cook sunny side up to desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes}. Divide polenta between plates. Top with sauce and spinach mixture. Place an egg on top of each, then garnish with reserved chorizo.